 Losses Africa\">{{cite web |title=War Losses (Africa) |url=http://encyclopedia.1914-1918-online.net/article/war_losses_africa |website=1914\u20131918 Online Encyclopedia |accessdate=23 May 2016}}</ref> || 750,000 || {{#expr: 750000 / 124.7 / 10000 round 2}}% ||\u2014 <!--Please do not change casualty numbers without discussion-->\n|-\n| align=left | {{flagicon|Albania|1914}} [[Principality of Albania|Albania]] {{Ref|Albania|ae}}\n| 0.8\n|\n|\n| See footnote\n| 70,000<ref>{{cite book |last=Tucker |first=Spencer C. |title=World War I: A Student Encyclopedia |authorlink= |year=2006 |publisher=ABC-CLIO |location=New York |isbn=9781851098798 | page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=TogXVHTlxG4C&printsec=frontcover&dq=isbn:9781851098798&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjJ-5Kd88_oAhWBhXIEHcrfDIoQuwUwAHoECAMQBw#v=onepage&q=albania&f=false 113]}}</ref>\n| 70,000\n| {{#expr: 70000 / 0.8 / 10000 round 2}}%\n| \u2014\n|-\n| align=left | {{flag|Denmark}} {{Ref|Denmark|af}}\n| 2.9\n|\n|See footnote\n| 700<ref name=\"Byarkivet i Horsens\">{{cite web |url=http://www.byarkivet-horsens.dk/Historie/Ubaadskrigen%201917.aspx |title=Byarkivet i Horsens |website=byarkivet-horsens.dk |accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref>\n|\n| 700\n| {{#expr: 722 / 2.9 / 10000 round 2}}%\n| \u2014\n|-\n| align=left | {{flag|Luxembourg}} {{Ref|Lux|ag}}\n| 0.3\n|\n| See footnote\n| 10<ref>{{cite book |ref=harv | first=Ernest | last=Faber | year=1932 | title=Luxemburg im Kriege 1914\u20131918 | location=Mersch|language=de|p=155}}</ref>\n|\n| 10\n| {{#expr: 10 / 0.3 / 10000 round 2}}%\n| \u2014 <!--Please do not change casualty numbers without discussion-->\n|-\n| align=left | {{flag|The Netherlands}} {{Ref|The Netherlands|ah}}\n| 6.3\n|\n|\n| 865<ref>Lith, Hans van. ''Plotseling een vreselijke knal''. Zaltbommel: Europese Bibliotheek, 2001, pp. 176\u2013177. (862 fisherman killed by the German [[U-boat Campaign (World War I)|U-boat Campaign]]</ref><ref>Lith, Hans van. ''Plotseling een vreselijke knal'', pp. 91\u201395. (3 civilians killed by accidental British bombing)</ref>\n|\n| 865\n| {{#expr: 865 / 6.3 / 10000 round 2}}%\n| \u2014\n|-\n| align=left | {{flag|Norway}} {{Ref|Norway|ai}}\n| 2.4\n|\n|\n| 1,180<ref name=\"International Labour Office p.29\" />\n|\n| 1,180\n| {{#expr: 1180 / 2.4 / 10000 round 2}}%\n| \u2014\n|-\n| align=left | {{flagdeco|Persia|1910}} [[Qajar Iran|Persia]] {{Ref|Persia|aj}}\n| 10.8\n|\n|\n| 9<ref>http://www.rmslusitania.info/people/lusitania-victims/</ref>\n| 2,000,000<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ward|first1=Steven R.|year=2014|title=Immortal, Updated Edition: A Military History of Iran and Its Armed Forces|publisher=Georgetown University Press|isbn=9781626160651|location=|pages=|ref={{harvid|Ward|2014}}}}, p.123: \"As the Great War came to its close in the fall of 1918, Iran's plight was woeful. The war had created an economic catastrophe, invading armies had ruined farmland and irrigation works, crops and livestock were stolen or destroyed, and peasants had been taken from their fields and forced to serve as laborers in the various armies. Famine killed as many as two million Iranians out of a population of little more than ten million while an influenza pandemic killed additional tens of thousands.\"</ref>\n| 2,000,009\n| {{#expr: 2000009 / 10.8 / 10000 round 2}}%\n| \u2014\n|-\n| align=left | {{flagdeco|Spain|1785}} [[Restoration (Spain)|Spain]] {{Ref|Spain|ak}}\n| 20.3\n|\n|\n| 100<ref>Ponce, Javier: [https://encyclopedia.1914-1918-online.net/article/spain Spain] , in: [https://encyclopedia.1914-1918-online.net/home/ 1914-1918-online. International Encyclopedia of the First World War]</ref>\n|\n| 100\n| {{#expr: 100 / 20.3 / 10000 round 2}}%\n| \u2014\n|-\n| align=left | {{flag|Sweden}} {{Ref|Sweden|al}}\n| 5.6\n| 34<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dn.se/arkiv/sondag/olof-palme-1884-1918-mannen-som-kunde-ha-blivit-en-svensk-fascistledare/ |newspaper=[[Dagens Nyheter]] |title=Olof Palme (1884 -1918). Mannen som kunde ha blivit en s